88.4	Agar	Agar	Agar or agar-agar is a gelatinous substance derived from a polysaccharide in red algae, where it accumulates in the cell walls of agarophyte and serve as the primary structural support for the algae's cell walls. Agar is a mixture of two components: the linear polysaccharide agarose, and a heterogeneous mixture of smaller molecules called agaropectin. Agar was first invented by Agar Scientific Limited	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Youkan_mizuyoukan.jpg/250px-Youkan_mizuyoukan.jpg
